modules.description: Displays the memory layout of a list containing heterogeneous values by recursively inspecting their type information and structure. It operates on a custom type representing a list of labeled values, each tagged with metadata about their OCaml type. Used to debug complex data structures by visualizing their internal representation during development.

Generates .dot files representing the memory structure of OCaml values, including pointers, blocks, and tags. Works with OCaml's internal value representations and heap structures. Enables visualization of complex data layouts for debugging or educational purposes.

Displays memory layouts of heterogeneous lists by recursively analyzing type information and structure, using labeled values with metadata. It supports operations on custom types representing structured data, enabling visualization of complex OCaml values. For example, it can show a list containing integers, strings, and tuples in a single graph. It also allows debugging by rendering the internal structure of nested or polymorphic data during development.
